events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Christian McCaffrey had two long touchdown runs and Ryan Burns threw a scoring pass in his first career start to lead No. 8 Stanford to a 26-13 victory over Kansas State on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCaffrey's 2 TDs lead No. 8 Stanford past KSU

events.name: Furman Paladins at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: The Spartans led just 21-13 early in the fourth and didn't put the game away until quarterback Tyler O'Connor threw a 12-yard TD pass to Jamal Lyles with 4:55 left in a 28-13 win over Furman.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spartans put Furman away late to avoid upset

events.name: Northwestern State Demons at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Seth Russell threw four TDs in less than a half, and No. 23 Baylor beat FCS team Northwestern State 55-7 in their first game since the dismissal of coach Art Briles.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor begins post-Briles era with blowout win

video.headline: Russell's terrific night continues for Baylor

headlines.description: Andy Davidson rushed for 121 yards and two touchdowns and Army piled up 329 yards on the ground to beat Temple 28-13 on Friday night in the opener for both teams.

headlines.description: Logan Woodside passed for three touchdowns and a career-high 371 yards Friday night to lead Toledo to a 31-10 win over Arkansas State in the season opener for both teams.

events.name: Cal Poly Mustangs at Nevada Wolf Pack
